# speckit/infrastructure/llm_serving/phi4-mini.Modelfile
#
# Builds a custom Ollama model on top of the base phi4-mini pull, with a
# larger context window baked in at the model level.
#
# WHY THIS EXISTS:
# Ollama defaults every model to a 2048-token context window unless told
# otherwise via `options.num_ctx` on each request. That per-request option is
# reliably honored on Ollama's native /api/generate and /api/chat endpoints
# (used by reasoning_agent.py and summary_agent.py), but is NOT guaranteed on
# the OpenAI-compatible /v1/chat/completions endpoint (used by
# intake_agent.py) across all Ollama versions. Since intake_agent.py sends
# the FULL text of an uploaded policy document in one prompt, it's the
# component most likely to silently exceed a 2048-token window — which
# would truncate the policy text with no error, not raise one.
#
# Building this custom model bakes num_ctx in at the model definition level,
# so every endpoint (generate, chat, and the OpenAI-compat layer) respects it
# consistently, regardless of whether the calling code also sets num_ctx
# per-request.
#
# USAGE:
#   1. Pull the base model first:
#        ollama pull phi4-mini
#   2. Build the custom model from this Modelfile:
#        ollama create phi4-mini-pa -f phi4-mini.Modelfile
#   3. Point the app at the custom model name instead of the bare tag —
#      in backend/.env.local (or wherever LLM_MODEL is set):
#        LLM_MODEL=phi4-mini-pa
#   4. Confirm it loads:
#        ollama run phi4-mini-pa "hi"
#
# If you skip this and use the bare `phi4-mini` tag, the app still sets
# num_ctx=8192 per-request wherever the Ollama API supports it (see
# reasoning_agent.py's _NUM_CTX constant) — this Modelfile is the belt to
# that suspenders for the one endpoint (intake_agent's chat-completions
# call) where the per-request option isn't guaranteed to apply.

FROM phi4-mini

# 8192 tokens comfortably covers the reasoning/summary prompts (policy
# requirement + up to 5 evidence chunks) and most real-world PA policy
# documents for intake extraction. Raise this further (e.g. 16384) if your
# policy documents run unusually long — check GPU VRAM headroom first, since
# KV-cache memory scales with context length.
PARAMETER num_ctx 8192

# Keep generation deterministic for clinical/compliance-sensitive output;
# the agents also set this per-request, but baking in a sane default here
# means any ad-hoc `ollama run phi4-mini-pa` testing behaves the same way.
PARAMETER temperature 0.1
